WEBVTT

00:00.578 --> 00:07.165
Sun Life Community Church came into being as the result of a compelling vision for a different kind of church.

00:07.945 --> 00:15.193
Interested in what we call the Sun Life, experiencing and sharing the life of God's Son?

00:15.934 --> 00:18.796
Perhaps your heart is burdened these days.

00:19.577 --> 00:28.306
We invite you to allow the Word of God through the words of this message to bring rest to your soul and joy to your heart.

00:32.258 --> 00:33.280
Got your Bibles with you?

00:34.521 --> 00:35.603
Pete, did you bring yours?

00:36.585 --> 00:39.409
It is great to have Pete and Joyce back with us here this morning.

00:39.790 --> 00:46.340
They have fought through some periods of illness here, and Pete said this morning, I'll be right here in this chair, long as I can.

00:46.400 --> 00:51.247
And so I'll be preaching right in that direction, because I've not seen your face in here for a while, Pete.

00:51.668 --> 00:53.551
But he sees mine every Sunday, right?

00:54.492 --> 00:58.258
Boy, they are faithful, live streamers at home,

00:58.466 --> 01:03.494
And so our views will be down one this week, but my views up one.

01:03.854 --> 01:05.276
And so I'm happy about that.

01:05.597 --> 01:06.718
Let's bow in prayer, shall we?

01:06.739 --> 01:09.543
Heavenly Father, we're about to open this Word of God.

01:09.603 --> 01:15.832
Forgive us when we ever take it for granted and think, well, everybody's got a Bible.

01:17.375 --> 01:19.858
Father in the world today, not everybody has a Bible.

01:20.559 --> 01:24.946
In this country, there are many, many Americans these days

01:25.026 --> 01:28.410
who do not own a Bible, have no intention of buying one.

01:28.470 --> 01:36.419
So Father, we are privileged people to have them in our hands and to realize that they contain the truth of God.

01:38.341 --> 01:40.383
They contain directions for our lives.

01:41.565 --> 01:46.911
So help us Father, by your Holy Spirit to just understand your word today.

01:48.092 --> 01:53.138
As we said in our bullet, then you are a masterful communicator.

01:54.114 --> 01:58.841
Father, just communicate to us through Your Word this morning for we ask it in Jesus' name.

01:59.923 --> 02:00.343
Amen.

02:01.405 --> 02:03.248
So we're in Acts chapter what?

02:05.010 --> 02:06.332
I talked to somebody last week.

02:06.352 --> 02:08.616
He said, are we ever going to get on Acts chapter 16?

02:09.878 --> 02:11.861
He says, I always read the chapter we're in.

02:11.881 --> 02:15.366
He says, and I've been reading Acts 16 again and again and again and again.

02:16.468 --> 02:19.011
Well, today's our last day in Acts chapter 16.

02:19.492 --> 02:23.378
But if I left it before we went through what we're going through today,

02:23.746 --> 02:25.609
the Holy Spirit would say, how dare you?

02:25.949 --> 02:26.690
How dare you?

02:27.211 --> 02:34.061
You spent this much time in Acts 16 and then you didn't actually get the punch out of it, so that's what we're doing today.

02:34.101 --> 02:46.418
We started last week looking at the passage, Acts 16, verse 16 through 40, a great, big, long extended story that we called the Philippian episode.

02:46.882 --> 02:55.336
And we said that so long and it contains so much stuff and there's two different ways of looking at it that we're going to have to have two parts to this message.

02:55.657 --> 02:56.879
First part was last week.

02:58.421 --> 03:00.705
It was called as the world turns.

03:01.266 --> 03:10.802
There's an incredible picture of how ungodly people work and think and function, how the world does its business.

03:11.298 --> 03:17.224
And the way the world does its business should be the exact opposite of how Christians do their business.

03:17.885 --> 03:23.670
And so this is what we're going to be comparing the other view today.

03:23.710 --> 03:29.416
But last week, we really looked at the way the world turns.

03:29.656 --> 03:31.158
As the world turns, we called it.

03:31.458 --> 03:35.142
So just to catch us up, let me give a brief recap.

03:35.162 --> 03:36.623
Not going to run it all through the screen.

03:36.663 --> 03:38.205
I'm just going to run it through your mind.

03:38.225 --> 03:39.666
This afternoon, we'll

03:40.418 --> 03:47.569
mail out this message and you can have these points yourself in front of you, but just a brief recap so we know what we're dealing with.

03:47.969 --> 03:50.413
Some of you maybe weren't here last week, but here we go.

03:50.794 --> 04:01.810
The story in this passage, Acts chapter 16, verse 16, really, just through verse 34 today, we see and we saw last week Paul and Silas

04:02.050 --> 04:04.696
began a ministry in Philippi.

04:04.777 --> 04:13.157
Before they got there, there had been no church, no mention of Jesus, no salvation, no evangelism, but they got to Philippi, they began a ministry.

04:13.818 --> 04:17.106
And as they began, a demon possessed slave girl

04:17.314 --> 04:25.925
came walking behind them regularly announcing that they were servants of God, announcing their divine mission.

04:26.245 --> 04:32.453
She even said, they have been sent by the Most High God to show you the way of salvation.

04:33.053 --> 04:34.155
Incredible statement.

04:35.757 --> 04:40.563
Then after many days, Luke tells us, Paul casts the evil spirit out of her.

04:41.404 --> 04:46.450
Now the slave girl's owners, they were outraged.

04:46.594 --> 04:57.065
They were using that evil spirit in that girl to cause her to be a fortune teller and they were selling her ability to anybody who would pay money for it.

04:58.046 --> 05:04.393
Paul cast that demon out of them and their chance of making money left and they were outraged.

05:04.473 --> 05:13.202
They dragged Paul and Silas before the city magistrates and there they made some outlandish accusations and in the heat of the moment

05:13.314 --> 05:22.606
The magistrates of the town ordered Saul and Paul and Silas to be stripped and beaten with rods.

05:23.227 --> 05:25.089
Paul and Silas were thrown into prison.

05:25.770 --> 05:29.334
At midnight, Paul and Silas were praying and singing hymns to God.

05:29.735 --> 05:32.398
It said all the other prisoners in there were listening to them.

05:34.081 --> 05:38.386
A violent earthquake shook the prison and loosed all the prisoners' bonds.

05:38.882 --> 05:42.027
The jailer now saw that the prison doors were open.

05:42.307 --> 05:45.272
He assumed that all the prisoners had escaped.

05:45.292 --> 05:53.606
He drew his sword and was planning to take his own life knowing that the Roman officials would take his life for dereliction of duty.

05:53.946 --> 05:58.233
So he's prepared to take his own life knowing this great tragedy has happened.

06:00.236 --> 06:04.663
Paul sees that and calls out and says, do not harm yourself.

06:05.244 --> 06:06.386
We're all here.

06:08.066 --> 06:09.228
Nobody had escaped.

06:10.049 --> 06:15.537
The jailer at that point fell to his knees and cried out, sirs, what must I do to be saved?

06:16.539 --> 06:20.305
Paul responded, believe in the Lord Jesus Christ and you will be saved.

06:20.325 --> 06:21.567
You and your whole household.

06:23.029 --> 06:26.654
Paul shared the full gospel with him and with all his household.

06:27.155 --> 06:32.764
And we're told that he and all the members of his family were baptized in the name of Jesus Christ that very night.

06:33.986 --> 06:35.208
The jailer washed their wounds.

06:35.788 --> 06:36.850
He fed them a meal.

06:37.506 --> 06:43.495
He was filled with joy, Luke says, because they had come to believe in God.

06:44.096 --> 06:45.158
Any of you believe in God?

06:46.159 --> 06:48.703
Any of you believe in Jesus Christ as your personal Savior?

06:49.304 --> 06:51.508
When you first believed were you filled with joy?

06:51.568 --> 06:53.511
Yes, yes.

06:53.591 --> 06:54.332
Well, so was he.

06:54.372 --> 06:57.637
It's the way it goes in Christ's world.

06:57.697 --> 07:01.764
It says, because he had come to believe in God, he and his whole household.

07:02.345 --> 07:05.810
Now, last week, we examined this

07:06.274 --> 07:07.936
Philippian episode.

07:07.956 --> 07:14.445
And as we did, we focused our attention upon the way the sinful world works.

07:14.826 --> 07:21.234
We need to know there's a way that the sinful world goes about getting from point A to point B.

07:21.575 --> 07:22.937
We need to recognize it.

07:23.838 --> 07:25.841
We need to know when it's happening.

07:26.461 --> 07:32.850
We also need to know when we are caught up in it and we start working our life in exactly the same way.

07:33.794 --> 07:35.175
We got to say, hey, that's not right.

07:35.195 --> 07:36.417
That's the way the world does it.

07:37.698 --> 07:39.640
So we looked at last week.

07:40.000 --> 07:44.605
And I shared with you two key world-identifying observations.

07:44.825 --> 07:54.995
It's like when you see these three things happen, in any of these three, you're dealing with the world, the fallen world, the sinful world, the against God world.

07:55.415 --> 08:02.322
The first one, we said, I identified a most common world-identifying reality.

08:02.530 --> 08:14.746
Just a basic reality that the world adopts as true, and whenever you see this being adopted, you know your got knees, your knee deep in the world's thinking, and that reality is this.

08:16.528 --> 08:17.450
It's all about money.

08:18.491 --> 08:20.033
It's all about money, it always is.

08:20.093 --> 08:21.495
The bottom line is the bottom line.

08:23.758 --> 08:29.906
Well, when we're seeing that, hearing that from people, just be sure you're not thinking it yourself,

08:30.530 --> 08:33.895
that the way you make every decision is, will it be profitable to me?

08:35.537 --> 08:40.584
When you see that, you can identify this is an aspect of the world I'm dealing with here.

08:41.185 --> 08:45.571
Secondly, we identified a most common world identifying strategy.

08:45.992 --> 08:54.243
How does the world go about dealing with its enemies, dealing particularly with the followers of Jesus Christ?

08:54.684 --> 08:56.447
And we just saw a couple of things last week.

08:56.487 --> 08:58.930
Number one, they isolate and they castigate.

08:59.394 --> 09:01.959
Isolate you say, they are not like us.

09:02.039 --> 09:02.821
They're different.

09:03.121 --> 09:08.071
And then they say harsh mean things about these folks, these believers.

09:08.772 --> 09:10.475
Secondly, they extrapolate.

09:10.536 --> 09:17.329
That means they take whatever it is you're doing and build a whole case out of it that goes way beyond what you were either doing or thinking.

09:17.850 --> 09:20.114
And as a result, they exaggerate.

09:20.642 --> 09:24.110
what a believer is about and what a believer is doing and what a threat they are.

09:24.290 --> 09:34.594
And when you hear that begin to happen, you're dealing with people whose minds are caught up in worldly thinking and following the worldly practice.

09:35.235 --> 09:40.146
And then lastly, we identified a common world identifying sequence.

09:40.418 --> 09:42.781
Like I said, how do they get from point A to point B?

09:43.122 --> 09:45.805
In this story, we really saw that sequence play out.

09:45.845 --> 09:49.710
Number one, situation happens and they jump the gun.

09:50.031 --> 09:51.693
Jump the conclusions, we might say.

09:52.033 --> 09:56.960
They ride a tide of emotion, not reason, but emotion.

09:57.601 --> 10:01.906
And in the process, they violate their own laws in the heat of that emotion.

10:02.187 --> 10:07.634
They get so worked up, so carried away, so enthused, they even forget that, hey, we're not allowed to do that.

10:08.354 --> 10:09.496
There's a stop sign there.

10:09.856 --> 10:12.380
Whoa, buzzed right through it 40 miles an hour.

10:13.282 --> 10:13.482
Why?

10:13.522 --> 10:17.789
Because that guy up there made a face at me, and I'm not going to let him get away with it.

10:17.809 --> 10:21.835
And the heat of emotion, forget the stop sign, forget any of the normal things.

10:22.256 --> 10:27.284
Just ride the tide of that emotion right into whatever comes.

10:28.866 --> 10:36.178
And we said, and whatever comes, and whatever came in this story, sometimes that gets you to a place where you embarrass yourself regularly.

10:37.570 --> 10:38.712
You just act like an idiot.

10:40.855 --> 10:43.358
Later on, you're embarrassed at yourself.

10:43.498 --> 10:44.399
Why did I do that?

10:44.480 --> 10:46.683
Well, because I just got completely out of control.

10:48.385 --> 10:59.641
And then once you recognize that, once these in the world recognize that, especially if they're people in control of anything, then as much as possible, they try to just sweep it under the rug.

11:00.822 --> 11:01.623
That never happened.

11:01.964 --> 11:02.404
Never happened.

11:02.424 --> 11:03.826
That wasn't really me doing that.

11:05.489 --> 11:06.450
I'm not like that.

11:07.618 --> 11:08.599
See, that's the word.

11:08.620 --> 11:09.721
There's a sequence.

11:10.963 --> 11:15.630
And we saw that play out in Acts 16 with all the unbelievers doing that stuff.

11:16.692 --> 11:21.259
So those three observations popped out, really, right out of the text.

11:22.120 --> 11:23.161
They're pretty hard to miss.

11:23.822 --> 11:26.126
They define the way the world works.

11:27.488 --> 11:36.882
Now, as I intimated a moment ago, sad to say, frequently or too often than we would like to admit, we ourselves can get caught up

11:37.378 --> 11:39.321
in the works of the world.

11:40.442 --> 11:42.905
We make the world's bottom line our bottom line.

11:45.569 --> 11:53.519
We make the world's strategy our strategy especially when we're dealing with what we perceive as our opponents our enemies.

11:55.161 --> 12:04.914
And we can fall into that same sequence of emotion fueled behavior that can lead us to do things that in our right mind we would never do.

12:06.594 --> 12:12.824
And we can do that because as we admitted to God a moment ago in our prayer, we're not perfect.

12:14.407 --> 12:19.595
And we can fall into the practices of this world if we are not careful.

12:20.577 --> 12:23.101
And we might think that's the way everybody functions.

12:24.222 --> 12:31.474
Well, now we take another look at this story and we find some agents of God going through that same situation, Paul and Silas.

12:31.895 --> 12:33.938
And the question is, how did they respond?

12:35.042 --> 12:44.214
What's a godly response when the world is doing what the world does when difficulties come that we haven't really had a hand in ourselves?

12:44.494 --> 12:45.976
How do Christians respond?

12:46.016 --> 12:47.318
Do we fight fire with fire?

12:48.700 --> 12:51.944
Well, that's a world way, but sometimes Christians use that.

12:53.426 --> 13:03.058
How do Christians, how does the Church of Jesus Christ respond when all around them, the world is working the way the world works?

13:03.650 --> 13:05.412
Well, here's what I want us to see today.

13:05.972 --> 13:11.057
See, so we're going to go back through the story and look at it from Paul and Silas' point of view.

13:11.097 --> 13:28.974
A further examination of this Philippian episode, and so we just call it, and we're going to focus today, not upon the way the world works, but rather upon the way Christ Church responds to the way the world works.

13:29.675 --> 13:30.235
So here we go.

13:30.315 --> 13:32.978
Paul and Silas will be our main example.

13:34.594 --> 13:38.038
Let's just follow them through and see how they handled things.

13:38.398 --> 13:41.882
And I hope as we go through this, some of you, let's see, should I pick out somebody?

13:42.443 --> 13:45.206
Some of you would say, you know, that's exactly what I would have done.

13:45.606 --> 13:47.268
That's exactly the way I handle stuff.

13:47.528 --> 13:51.613
That's the first thing that popped into my mind when I was in a situation like that.

13:52.113 --> 13:53.355
Boy, I hope so.

13:54.296 --> 14:00.082
Because this happened 2,000 years ago and Christians have had 2,000 years to kind of refine

14:00.642 --> 14:06.271
their understanding of how the Church of Jesus Christ is to function in this fallen broken world.

14:06.772 --> 14:13.282
So as I go through this, maybe a whole bunch of you say, of course, of course, that's the way we do it.

14:13.522 --> 14:17.208
Paul and Silas might have been the first ones, but we got that nailed down now.

14:18.069 --> 14:21.074
So get prepared to pat yourself on the back.

14:22.434 --> 14:30.903
or to ask the person next to you, would you just pat me on the back because you might as well call me Saul or call me Silas because this is all familiar stuff.

14:31.124 --> 14:35.829
But let's go through it anyway, just in case there might be somebody here that needs some insight.

14:36.810 --> 14:38.211
Let's see how they handled things.

14:39.853 --> 14:45.699
And I'm sure some of their responses might catch any one of us completely by surprise.

14:46.981 --> 14:51.666
And all of them require great measures of God's grace

14:51.874 --> 14:55.400
for us to live out in the world today or any day.

14:56.081 --> 15:00.308
So as you have on your notes now, we're catching up to where you've got something to fill in.

15:00.728 --> 15:09.021
There are five specific Christ honoring responses that I see in this story, this passage.

15:09.703 --> 15:16.614
Five ways that Paul and Silas responded to the workings of the world that they were caught up in.

15:17.074 --> 15:17.715
So here we go.

15:17.755 --> 15:19.378
Number one,

15:19.906 --> 15:24.433
In response to Numa's nudge, they obeyed.

15:25.295 --> 15:29.341
How many of you have ever felt a nudge from the Holy Spirit from Numa Himself?

15:31.284 --> 15:34.950
We've been talking about that a lot the last six or seven years here.

15:35.591 --> 15:38.535
In response to Numa's nudge, they obeyed.

15:38.776 --> 15:43.043
Here's the verse that I believe shows that and then we'll explain it.

15:43.463 --> 15:47.730
Verse 18 of chapter 16, Luke says, finally,

15:48.354 --> 15:54.803
See, this servant girl was following them day after day after day after day, and she was announcing, I mean, here they are.

15:55.043 --> 15:56.285
These are workers of God.

15:56.525 --> 15:58.348
They will show you the way to salvation.

15:58.648 --> 16:04.176
Who knows how many people started to follow Paul and Silas down to their meeting place as a result.

16:04.236 --> 16:10.264
She might as well have had a megaphone in her hand announcing who they were.

16:12.147 --> 16:13.949
Luke says she did this for many days.

16:14.670 --> 16:17.234
Finally, Paul became so

16:17.410 --> 16:24.602
troubled that he said to the Spirit that was in her, in the name of Jesus Christ, I command you to come out of her."

16:26.284 --> 16:27.827
And the Bible says the Spirit left.

16:29.149 --> 16:40.687
And she was left devoid of this ability that she seemingly had had to tell people's future and let her owners charge money to have a seance almost with her.

16:40.748 --> 16:42.290
That Spirit left

16:42.466 --> 16:47.713
Obviously, there was such a change in her that her owners immediately know, man, she's no good for us anymore.

16:48.895 --> 16:50.577
She's no, look at the smile on her face.

16:50.938 --> 16:52.560
Nobody's got to believe a girl like that.

16:56.485 --> 16:58.248
Now, let me tell you this morning.

17:00.230 --> 17:06.780
I believe that this was not the result of Paul just saying, I can't take this anymore.

17:07.761 --> 17:09.043
That girl's bugging me.

17:10.585 --> 17:11.506
It's annoying.

17:14.626 --> 17:23.717
See, after all, Luke tells us that this spirit possessed slave girl had been following them and trumpeting their cause for many days.

17:26.701 --> 17:29.204
If you were Paul, wouldn't that have bothered you day one?

17:30.545 --> 17:31.326
Day one?

17:31.386 --> 17:44.242
Her notoriety in Philippi certainly drew much attention to them and perhaps caused many of the city's citizens

17:44.770 --> 17:46.693
to come and just check things out.

17:47.694 --> 17:49.056
Well, let's listen to this guy.

17:50.057 --> 17:51.079
Let's see what he's saying.

17:52.761 --> 17:53.522
So why?

17:53.602 --> 18:01.272
Why on this day did Paul take this dramatic step, a step that brought severe consequences with it?

18:03.375 --> 18:10.825
Why on this day was Paul so troubled that he took action?

18:13.569 --> 18:14.450
Luke tells us.

18:14.786 --> 18:18.350
It was because he was troubled, deeply troubled.

18:18.771 --> 18:20.153
Now let me tell you something.

18:20.173 --> 18:22.656
I might have hinted at this a week or so ago.

18:23.056 --> 18:29.444
The Greek word here that Luke uses for Paul was whatever, troubled.

18:31.747 --> 18:39.417
It's only used twice in the entire New Testament, both times by Luke, once in chapter four and one right here.

18:40.298 --> 18:43.442
So when the English translators are trying to translate

18:43.650 --> 18:55.142
our scripture from Greek into English, they got a word here, a Greek word that's only used twice in the whole New Testament, only used by Luke and only used in the book of Acts.

18:55.663 --> 19:06.414
And Paul was something that caused this dramatic action on his part.

19:07.676 --> 19:13.522
And this something he was is explained by a Greek word that is used very, very little.

19:14.722 --> 19:25.858
And so the context doesn't really help us with what the word means because Paul was something and he commanded the spirit to come out of her.

19:26.799 --> 19:30.484
He was so something that he just had to deal with it.

19:32.347 --> 19:35.992
Even though days and days and days and days went by and he didn't deal with it at all.

19:36.332 --> 19:39.377
He wasn't so something on those days.

19:40.899 --> 19:43.122
So what is going on here?

19:44.130 --> 19:49.939
See the NIV, the new international version, translators, they've used several words.

19:50.940 --> 19:54.946
Every now and then the NIV brings out a new version.

19:56.668 --> 19:59.072
Linda and I hate that.

19:59.092 --> 20:14.034
The NIV first came out when we were in, right at the end of Wheaton College in starting seminary, some of our seminary professors were actually shared in the translation of it, and it was an awesome up-to-date

20:14.466 --> 20:20.374
accurate translation of the scripture, and that was over 50 years ago.

20:21.876 --> 20:27.985
And the NIV is forever their translation committee upgrading a word here, changing a word there.

20:28.385 --> 20:32.891
In fact, two weeks ago, the scripture we put right on our screen had this word.

20:35.054 --> 20:37.618
And it's one that I would find the most objectionable

20:37.890 --> 20:44.300
of all the possibilities, but we put it on the screen because that's what was in the current NIV text.

20:44.320 --> 20:47.805
And it says, finally, Paul got so annoyed.

20:49.848 --> 20:50.369
Annoyed.

20:50.429 --> 20:51.871
Now, there's something godly.

20:53.413 --> 20:56.438
How many of you have ever been so godly you've gotten annoyed?

21:00.584 --> 21:02.106
I think of why that word.

21:02.948 --> 21:03.809
Why that word?

21:03.829 --> 21:07.154
The earlier version said he was troubled.

21:07.906 --> 21:08.767
He was troubled.

21:08.827 --> 21:10.909
Now, that's a word that doesn't really tell us much at all.

21:10.989 --> 21:14.793
Annoyed kind of means, man, I tell you, she's driving me nuts.

21:14.853 --> 21:17.775
If you don't stop her, I'm going to hit her with a clump.

21:20.818 --> 21:22.900
That sounds kind of fleshly, doesn't it?

21:23.661 --> 21:27.485
Can't you just see the Apostle Paul starting to work for God in a pagan place?

21:27.865 --> 21:29.226
Lydia comes to Christ.

21:29.486 --> 21:31.789
They have great ministry, success.

21:31.849 --> 21:37.554
They're living in Lydia's beautiful home, and they're continuing their ministry, and all of a sudden,

21:37.634 --> 21:41.638
Paul is overcome by human flesh and just gets ticked off.

21:41.658 --> 21:42.219
Annoyed.

21:44.961 --> 21:54.251
I can't believe how any translator of the New Testament would choose that English word as being something that would help us understand the story.

21:56.413 --> 21:56.893
What if?

21:58.355 --> 21:59.796
Let's all be translators here.

22:00.898 --> 22:05.362
What if I choose the word stirred?

22:06.178 --> 22:17.052
as in Paul was greatly stirred by the Holy Spirit, stirred, moved by the Holy Spirit.

22:18.133 --> 22:26.163
What if that day was the day that Numa himself said to Paul in effect, Paul, would you free that poor girl from her bondage?

22:27.665 --> 22:30.548
She has done about as much good for you as she possibly can.

22:30.849 --> 22:32.551
Would you free her now?

22:34.053 --> 22:34.994
Deliver her.

22:36.130 --> 22:40.797
And the Spirit made that impression so strong on Paul that he couldn't deny it.

22:42.139 --> 22:44.623
And he turns to her and he frees her.

22:45.945 --> 22:48.630
And don't you think she just trotted on right after them?

22:49.090 --> 22:51.454
Now completely free from that evil Spirit.

22:51.835 --> 22:54.739
Now probably wanting to become one of them.

22:58.445 --> 23:01.650
You see, we here at Sun Life Community Church believe strongly

23:01.730 --> 23:06.077
in the moment by moment leading of the Holy Spirit in our lives.

23:07.039 --> 23:16.094
Certainly we believe that all transformational moments come as a result of His actions in our lives.

23:17.777 --> 23:20.722
For every believer, the Holy Spirit

23:20.898 --> 23:24.342
is their companion, their guide, their influencer.

23:24.722 --> 23:26.344
He is God with them.

23:26.644 --> 23:34.212
There is nothing that has ever happened in any of our lives since the moment of our salvation, which was, of course, transformational.

23:35.394 --> 23:39.738
Nothing transformational that doesn't have the Holy Spirit's fingerprints all over it.

23:40.779 --> 23:41.580
That's what he does.

23:41.740 --> 23:42.902
Something dramatic comes.

23:43.302 --> 23:44.283
Something happens.

23:44.764 --> 23:46.445
This is a Holy Spirit-led thing.

23:46.826 --> 23:50.770
The apostle Paul was so troubled, distressed,

23:50.882 --> 23:52.845
It wasn't like any other day.

23:52.905 --> 24:04.360
And now today at this point, without any trouble at all, I can hear the Holy Spirit saying to her, Paul, today is the day.

24:05.041 --> 24:13.011
Release that poor girl from her bondage and even demonstrate the power of Jesus Christ over the devil himself.

24:13.992 --> 24:14.333
Do it.

24:15.274 --> 24:15.634
Do it.

24:17.637 --> 24:18.418
And Paul did.

24:19.394 --> 24:28.588
Now I have no doubt that Paul was pretty sure that obeying the Spirit's voice would bring some pretty severe consequences.

24:30.350 --> 24:31.632
Have you ever felt that way yourself?

24:32.373 --> 24:42.188
You know, there's something God wants you to do and you think inside your own little head, oh, if I do that, if I do that, he will, she will, they will.

24:42.668 --> 24:43.890
I won't be a

24:44.802 --> 24:48.526
If I do that, and yet you know it's something God wants you to do.

24:48.606 --> 24:51.549
Maybe you've read a scripture that just knocks you between the eyes.

24:51.930 --> 24:59.778
Maybe you hear the voice of the Spirit so distinctly that it's almost like he's moving you in the direction of doing this thing.

25:01.840 --> 25:04.724
We gotta believe Paul knew there would be consequences to this.

25:07.927 --> 25:09.409
But that was the whole point, wasn't it?

25:11.050 --> 25:14.354
You see, the members of Christ's church,

25:15.298 --> 25:27.114
Taking Paul and Paul and Silas as their examples, the members of Christchurch obey once they are nudged by Numa in some particular way.

25:28.256 --> 25:29.597
It's a fundamental response.

25:30.859 --> 25:36.006
That response distinguishes them from the way the world works.

25:37.708 --> 25:40.732
The world is never directed by the Spirit of God.

25:41.494 --> 25:44.818
The world is, there's no contact, there's no connection.

25:44.898 --> 25:47.802
between a lost soul and the spirit of God.

25:47.942 --> 25:54.010
Until that lost soul is made new by the spirit of God, that relationship can begin.

25:54.070 --> 25:59.397
Only a believer receives these kinds of impressions.

25:59.557 --> 26:02.841
We call them nudges from the Holy Spirit.

26:04.383 --> 26:09.610
And when we feel one, it's essential that we obey it.

26:11.252 --> 26:12.754
It's a fundamental response.

26:13.602 --> 26:20.091
You see, believers obey because they believe that they are hearing the voice of God.

26:21.833 --> 26:25.178
They believe that they are hearing the Spirit's direction.

26:25.758 --> 26:41.980
And they trust, even as they're obeying, which is going to maybe walk them into some unknown territory, they obey and they trust that the Spirit will lead in some productive and God-honoring way.

26:42.301 --> 26:43.282
That's what He does.

26:44.194 --> 26:57.594
He leads us into and through all kinds of things, but we obey Him because we believe it's His voice and we trust Him when we yield ourselves to follow.

26:57.634 --> 27:04.224
Some years later, the Apostle Paul would write these words in his epistle to the Galatian church.

27:04.624 --> 27:13.778
He says, and he could be thinking back on this moment or on many moments in his life, he said, since we live by the Spirit,

27:14.018 --> 27:16.602
Let us keep in step with the Spirit.

27:18.064 --> 27:37.676
We're watching Paul keep in step with the Spirit that day, stirred to do something that no doubt is going to bring trouble and may be going to upset some of the good stuff they have going already, but it's the Spirit's voice.

27:37.696 --> 27:39.539
And the Spirit knows what He's doing.

27:40.400 --> 27:41.682
And my job is to

27:41.794 --> 27:43.356
keep in step with Him.

27:43.757 --> 27:47.162
And so that's the first Christ honoring response we see here.

27:48.264 --> 27:51.188
In response to Numa's nudge, they obeyed.

27:51.228 --> 27:52.810
Here's the second one moving along.

27:54.212 --> 27:58.479
In response to the pain of persecution, they endured.

28:03.006 --> 28:05.710
We wish this wasn't even illustrated in the Bible.

28:05.750 --> 28:09.455
Christian shouldn't ever experience the pain of persecution, should we?

28:10.316 --> 28:11.378
I mean, for heaven's sakes.

28:11.938 --> 28:12.840
We've been born again.

28:12.900 --> 28:14.222
We've been forgiven of our sins.

28:14.283 --> 28:15.445
We are God's people.

28:15.786 --> 28:18.411
God protects us like He protected Job of all.

28:18.451 --> 28:19.132
Does He not?

28:20.234 --> 28:22.338
Does He not keep all harm from our dwelling?

28:22.358 --> 28:24.543
Does He not keep all sickness out of our body?

28:26.005 --> 28:28.410
You don't talk to me about the pain of persecution.

28:28.470 --> 28:32.178
We're victorious Christians.

28:34.041 --> 28:34.482
Well,

28:35.170 --> 28:37.092
Here's what it says, verse 22 to 24.

28:37.412 --> 28:47.902
The magistrates, after Paul and Silas had been drug in front of them, and the crowd is screaming at them, the magistrates ordered them to be stripped and beaten.

28:48.683 --> 28:51.966
After they had been severely flogged, they were thrown into prison.

28:52.667 --> 28:57.312
The jailer put them in an inner cell, like so, man, there's no way you're getting out of here.

28:57.732 --> 29:03.858
Put them in an inner cell, and on top of it, he fashioned their feet in stocks.

29:06.306 --> 29:07.368
Now that was pretty severe.

29:09.310 --> 29:11.694
Paul knew there would be some kind of disruption here.

29:12.976 --> 29:20.266
Anytime we take a step like this, when we change the course of events, we know there's going to be repercussions.

29:21.668 --> 29:24.913
But I doubt that Paul saw all of this coming.

29:26.415 --> 29:30.100
You see, after all, he and Silas were Roman citizens.

29:31.142 --> 29:34.226
This was a major city under Roman jurisdiction.

29:34.722 --> 29:48.086
Of course, the owners of that slave girl would create a fuss and might well drag them into court, but Roman justice would prevail once they explained everything to the duly appointed magistrates.

29:49.007 --> 29:57.362
Oh, it would mess up their ministry for a while, but come on, we know how Rome works, we're citizens, we have rights, all of this, and

29:58.338 --> 30:00.020
But things didn't work out that way at all.

30:00.060 --> 30:04.505
They didn't just get thrown into court and have to defend themselves in some way.

30:05.667 --> 30:09.932
The owners of the slave girl actually went berserk.

30:09.952 --> 30:18.882
They stirred up the townspeople, and by the time the magistrates even got involved, a full-blown riot had broken out.

30:20.704 --> 30:21.425
What are you going to do?

30:22.606 --> 30:25.650
If you're a magistrate, trying to keep Roman

30:26.434 --> 30:29.657
civil society as well as Roman law.

30:31.579 --> 30:35.463
So at that point, nobody asked Paul and Silas about their citizenship status.

30:36.484 --> 30:41.008
The magistrate skirted the law and simply sought to appease the crowd.

30:41.709 --> 30:49.717
Things got completely out of hand as sometimes happens when the world system is running the show.

30:51.418 --> 30:55.122
And so, by following the spirit's lead,

30:55.202 --> 31:04.135
Paul and Silas wound up bruised and buddy, bloody with their hands and chains in their feet in a set of wooden stalks.

31:08.181 --> 31:19.558
Now truth be told, that has happened more than once over the years when members of Christ church choose to obey some nudge from Numa.

31:21.061 --> 31:22.002
When you think about it,

31:22.690 --> 31:25.373
That's exactly what happened to Jesus himself.

31:26.314 --> 31:32.740
He followed the Spirit through this world and suffered like no man has ever suffered.

31:36.704 --> 31:42.090
The events of that day and night help fulfill one of the deep longings of Paul's heart.

31:43.851 --> 31:46.454
You might say this was a wonderful thing that happened to him.

31:47.295 --> 31:48.316
Say, are you kidding me?

31:48.356 --> 31:50.418
Well, let me share this with you.

31:50.530 --> 31:54.214
Paul revealed that longing in his heart in the letter.

31:54.274 --> 31:59.520
He would one day write to the church in this very city of Philippi, his letter to the Philippians.

31:59.581 --> 32:09.012
He wrote Philippians chapter three, verse 10, I want to know Christ and the fellowship of sharing in his sufferings.

32:09.652 --> 32:10.293
Guess what, Paul?

32:12.916 --> 32:14.578
That longing's been fulfilled.

32:15.362 --> 32:16.664
Man, are you suffering?

32:16.704 --> 32:18.626
You were beaten within an inch of your life.

32:18.906 --> 32:22.531
You're thrown in jail without even being heard from.

32:22.551 --> 32:28.178
And who knows what's coming tomorrow?

32:30.340 --> 32:41.554
You see, those who read those words in the church in Philippi when Paul sent that letter, some of them no doubt were present during those initial days of ministry.

32:43.586 --> 32:47.710
And they said, boy, when I read that from Paul, I think the night of the earthquake.

32:49.452 --> 32:57.140
I think of that whole episode where he and Silas were treated so badly, certainly Paul.

32:58.582 --> 33:02.146
Now he's telling us that's long been a desire of his heart.

33:02.947 --> 33:07.732
To just share in the sufferings of Christ is like, boy, he shared that night.

33:09.093 --> 33:10.034
So did Silas.

33:13.026 --> 33:28.942
And hopefully, let me just say, perhaps that liberated slave girl was one who nodded her head in agreement in the fellowship of that church family when they read that letter.

33:28.962 --> 33:32.325
I sense that that was the way Paul viewed the situation.

33:33.466 --> 33:41.714
He and Silas were sharing in the sufferings of Christ and what could be more Christ honoring than that.

33:43.650 --> 33:53.303
Now, the fact that that's really how they were looking at it as they sat there that night in prison, bloodied and battered is seen by this next response.

33:55.667 --> 34:00.493
You see, the response, a Christ-honoring response is this.

34:01.014 --> 34:12.530
In moments, in response to moments of uncertainty, they, that is, Paul and Silas and all true believers since, praised.

34:13.282 --> 34:13.863
praise.

34:14.784 --> 34:23.577
Acts chapter 16 verse 25, about midnight Paul and Silas were praying and singing hymns to God and the other prisoners were listening to them.

34:24.759 --> 34:26.261
What an interesting thing to tell us.

34:27.323 --> 34:31.890
See certainly nothing that Paul would have normally expected had happened.

34:33.452 --> 34:40.082
He and Silas had been hit by a runaway train of human emotions and injustices.

34:40.354 --> 34:43.339
They had no way of knowing what would come next.

34:44.941 --> 34:48.186
Uncertain indeed was their future.

34:48.527 --> 34:53.734
And in response, we say to moments of uncertainty, what's happening now?

34:53.795 --> 34:55.277
What's going to tomorrow bring?

34:55.297 --> 34:57.681
They praise God.

34:58.642 --> 35:09.138
In the midst of those circumstances, they took refuge, I would say, in their uncertain time in the certainties of God.

35:10.594 --> 35:11.135
they knew.

35:11.155 --> 35:28.280
They knew, like we know ourselves, that their God was brilliantly wise, profoundly wise, breathtakingly strategic, brilliantly tactical, tirelessly vigilant, preeminently trustworthy and unceasingly creative and unfailingly faithful.

35:28.761 --> 35:32.567
That's only a handful of the identities of God that we've put together.

35:32.867 --> 35:34.910
They knew God to be that way.

35:35.151 --> 35:40.018
They were singing hymns of truth to God, made me think this morning.

35:40.194 --> 35:41.616
We have 30 of those traits.

35:41.696 --> 35:43.538
We ought to choose a song for each one.

35:45.500 --> 36:00.536
Have 30 songs when in times of uncertainty and stress, when we want to remind ourselves of the goodness and greatness, the attributes of our Heavenly Father, here's a hymn we can sing, a song we can sing that just identifies.

36:01.056 --> 36:02.218
I mean, that'd take us all night.

36:04.260 --> 36:06.322
So we wouldn't have to worry about other stuff.

36:06.626 --> 36:11.350
were just singing praise to God in the midst of uncertain times.

36:13.633 --> 36:36.274
I have a feeling this Philippian episode was one of the events of Paul's life that he must have had in mind when he wrote these words in his first letter to the Thessalonians, 1 Thessalonians chapter 5, verses 16 to 18, he says, be joyful always, pray continually, give thanks in all circumstances

36:36.994 --> 36:40.098
For this is God's will for you in Christ Jesus.

36:42.841 --> 36:43.982
Don't complain and gripe.

36:44.503 --> 36:50.990
Whatever you're in, even the thing that's happened to you or the thing you're not sure is going to happen to you next.

36:52.232 --> 36:53.213
Be joyful always.

36:53.873 --> 36:56.156
God is God and God is good.

36:57.017 --> 37:01.362
Pray continually, never break fellowship with your almighty heavenly Father.

37:01.762 --> 37:04.246
Give thanks in all circumstances.

37:04.466 --> 37:11.476
Oh God, I can't see what all is going on, but boy, I thank you for your faithfulness to me.

37:16.003 --> 37:18.907
For this is God's will for you.

37:20.570 --> 37:31.506
I have a feeling that maybe some of them who had seen these things in Philippi were there when this

37:32.290 --> 37:37.576
when that letter to the Philippians came when it was read.

37:40.280 --> 37:42.723
Maybe some of those fellow prisoners were there.

37:44.345 --> 37:45.426
Those guys didn't run away.

37:47.108 --> 37:48.310
Does that not make you curious?

37:49.791 --> 37:53.115
They had been listening to Paul and Silas all night long.

37:53.516 --> 37:58.482
How many of them had actually embraced what Paul and Silas were singing about?

37:59.426 --> 38:20.029
How many of them saw the earthquake realized a miracle was taking place, and they themselves were caught up in all that, and maybe a few of them, when Paul's letter to the Philippians came, they were actually in that church themselves, hearing Paul talk about the fellowship of his sufferings with Christ.

38:21.551 --> 38:27.858
We could see all these people having, they're part of the story, and maybe they stayed part of the story,

38:28.418 --> 38:29.600
for the rest of their lives.

38:30.241 --> 38:39.214
So praising God, when those who are part of the world's system would be cursing God, is truly a God honoring response.

38:39.234 --> 38:41.317
Well, here's just fourth one, we'll move right along here.

38:41.658 --> 38:46.705
In response to a ministry opportunity, they engaged themselves.

38:47.026 --> 38:48.007
They jumped right in.

38:50.211 --> 38:53.515
The Philippian jailer, it says he was about to kill himself.

38:53.776 --> 38:55.218
Paul says, don't harm yourself.

38:55.426 --> 38:58.730
The jailor falls down before them and says, what must I do to be saved?

38:59.470 --> 39:01.332
And they tell him to believe in the Lord Jesus.

39:02.353 --> 39:08.941
I've got to confess that this week my take as it were on this encounter has changed.

39:09.381 --> 39:21.394
How many of you would agree with what I thought for a good part of my life that Paul and Silas here just took advantage of a situation and twisted around to make it a gospel presentation?

39:23.330 --> 39:27.354
How many of you think that jailer when he says, what must I do to be saved?

39:27.694 --> 39:30.917
He's actually asking, what do I do to keep alive?

39:33.580 --> 39:37.744
See, he was going to kill himself because he thought all his prisoners had escaped.

39:38.945 --> 39:42.128
Do you think he was still going to kill himself after Paul says, nobody's escaped?

39:42.148 --> 39:42.728
They're all here.

39:43.329 --> 39:44.110
It's a miracle.

39:44.570 --> 39:46.132
You're off the hook.

39:46.152 --> 39:47.433
You're still a good jailer.

39:48.254 --> 39:52.818
Just get new doors and lock them up and you'll be in trouble with nobody.

39:52.898 --> 39:55.041
It just went through my mind.

39:55.102 --> 40:02.453
It would be stupid of him after he knew nobody escaped to still be thinking his life was threatened.

40:05.418 --> 40:08.824
What is the possibility he was asking the real question?

40:10.466 --> 40:16.977
This slave girl had been saying, these men will show you the way to be saved, the way of salvation.

40:17.277 --> 40:20.242
He's seeing miracles right in front of him.

40:20.450 --> 40:27.660
And he's overwhelmed with truth like he's never encountered before, the power of God like he's never encountered before.

40:27.960 --> 40:32.847
He drops on his knees in front of these men who've been sent by the Most High God.

40:33.247 --> 40:34.228
And he says, how about me?

40:34.288 --> 40:35.390
How can I be part of that?

40:36.872 --> 40:38.013
How can I be saved?

40:39.275 --> 40:40.817
How can I be saved?

40:41.358 --> 40:47.066
That he actually was seeking spiritual salvation, not physical salvation at all.

40:48.848 --> 40:50.450
It was a genuine ministry.

40:50.722 --> 40:51.543
opportunity.

40:52.244 --> 41:05.259
And Paul and Barnabas jumped right into it, and they just said, here it is, man, believe in the name of the Lord Jesus Christ, and you will be saved, spiritually saved, made new in Christ.

41:05.559 --> 41:14.770
And then it says, Paul went to the house and they talk much more, the words of the Lord to them, until they came to a place where they

41:15.394 --> 41:21.121
They confessed Christ they were baptized the entire household was and became just a marvelous thing.

41:21.922 --> 41:25.607
A whole house of pagan people saved and baptized.

41:28.150 --> 41:34.318
Paul was always ready to give the answer that is Jesus Christ.

41:34.898 --> 41:40.946
Later on Paul would write to the Romans and in chapter 1 verse 16 he would say, I am not ashamed.

41:41.378 --> 41:44.342
never been ashamed of the gospel of Jesus Christ.

41:44.743 --> 41:48.489
It is the power of God and to salvation to all who will believe."

41:50.431 --> 41:52.555
And boy, it sure was that night.

41:54.317 --> 41:54.838
Last thing.

41:55.539 --> 42:02.870
Number five, a God-honoring response in response to their spiritual harvest, they rejoiced.

42:03.891 --> 42:04.633
Great joy.

42:05.173 --> 42:06.415
Fill that whole household.

42:06.495 --> 42:08.338
Paul and Silas were part of it.

42:08.482 --> 42:17.956
A meal was prepared, joy was expressed, and it says right there, the jailer was filled with joy for he had come to believe in God.

42:18.476 --> 42:21.821
See, it doesn't say he was filled with joy because all his prisoners were still there.

42:22.482 --> 42:26.888
He was filled with joy because his superiors weren't going to be after him anymore.

42:27.249 --> 42:31.234
He was filled with joy because he had come to believe in God.

42:31.635 --> 42:33.277
He and his whole household.

42:34.980 --> 42:36.562
I wonder how many times

42:36.834 --> 42:39.518
that man and his family retold that story.

42:41.360 --> 42:46.367
How many times have others over the years since told that story for them?

42:47.269 --> 42:52.756
How many times has it been told and how many times will it be told in heaven itself?

42:54.479 --> 42:57.062
And is it not always told with joy?

42:58.024 --> 42:59.826
Look at what God has done.

43:01.282 --> 43:06.389
Jesus himself said the words that confirm the universality of that response.

43:06.670 --> 43:15.322
He said in Luke chapter 15, seven, there is great joy in heaven over a single sinner who repents.

43:17.745 --> 43:21.451
True Christians rejoice when people get saved.

43:22.733 --> 43:29.362
True Christians rejoice deeply when individuals make steps of growth

43:29.506 --> 43:37.094
and obey the Lord in some way, even if it causes them harm, they believe and they trust and they stay firm.

43:37.895 --> 43:40.238
There's just great rejoicing in that.

43:41.259 --> 43:43.061
We could tell stories right here today.

43:45.023 --> 43:54.994
How many of you right in this room even today have brought me incredible joy, Linda and I, through the years, your faithfulness,

43:55.362 --> 43:59.607
Your trust, your endurance at times of real difficult stuff.

44:00.589 --> 44:05.815
You're continuing to move forward when right in front of you were only question marks.

44:07.618 --> 44:12.804
What a delight, what a delight to see people like that, to know people like that.

44:14.066 --> 44:16.229
Heaven itself rejoices.

44:17.551 --> 44:23.378
And so as we conclude our examination of Acts chapter 16, let me just live you with this final thought.

44:24.482 --> 44:32.495
the works of the world that hopefully we have tucked away in our mind what those are like, or we can review them when we come back here.

44:33.016 --> 44:40.007
The works of the world and the responses of Christ's church have nothing in common.

44:42.751 --> 44:47.338
And if it ever looks like they do, we have a problem.

44:48.901 --> 44:49.842
We have a problem.

44:50.463 --> 44:52.306
Let's bow in prayer, Heavenly Father,

44:52.546 --> 44:57.551
How good to know that the works of God are so different from the works of the world.

44:58.372 --> 45:05.579
The works of the world have been orchestrated and devised by the enemy of our faith himself, Satan himself.

45:09.463 --> 45:16.810
And the responses that are regularly made among the body of believers are so different.

45:18.792 --> 45:20.914
The responses that honor you,

45:21.794 --> 45:31.967
Father, we've just looked at five of them this morning, but I pray that our response to you even this moment would be honoring to you.

45:32.027 --> 45:38.315
And all our responses in the week ahead, may they be honoring to you.

45:38.835 --> 45:47.346
May they fall into the pattern of those who hear your spirit's voice, who obey what he says, who

45:48.770 --> 45:56.038
Open their arms to whatever the consequences are and trust you regardless of how things seem.

45:57.760 --> 46:00.583
Oh, Father, bless this congregation, each one here today.

46:00.964 --> 46:17.362
Those who are listening, watching, Father, all your people everywhere, bless them with the kind of heart and spirit that they just naturally, by your spirit, respond in Christ-honoring ways in every circumstance we're in.

46:18.434 --> 46:20.056
Thank you for Paul and Silas.

46:21.158 --> 46:27.387
Oh, what great examples they've been, what great courage they've shown, what great faithfulness they demonstrated.

46:28.208 --> 46:33.576
We thank you for them and for preserving the accounts of their lives for us.

46:35.439 --> 46:40.466
May we just be blessed greatly by it, for we ask it in Jesus' name.

